@ThinkingandTinkering I was careless. The cheapest way to buy HCL here (Ohio) is an off-brand toilet bowl cleaner, about $1.50 a pint. I reckoned it must be diluted down and carelessly neglected to check. I used a small container to remove rust from some small tools. I left the open container on my workbench for a day or so and when I returned anything within about 5 feet was covered in flash rust. Things that had been in my dampish basement for years but had not rusted were covered in it. 

Anyway, a displaced Brit living in Ohio loves your channel. Thanks for your efforts.

Ian
